# Windows Encoding

On Windows, never save repository text files as UTF-16 LE.

- PowerShell writes: `[System.IO.File]::WriteAllText($path, $content, (New-Object System.Text.UTF8Encoding $false))`
- Or `Set-Content -Encoding utf8` (verify no BOM issues on JSON/YAML)
- UTF-16 corruption breaks `.gitignore`, JSON, YAML, and `cargo`/`npm` parsers

After bulk edits on Windows, spot-check affected files open correctly in git diff.

When `scripts/check-file-encoding.py` lands (TM.6), run it before push.
